  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Shipping Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Shipping Operations Executive (Dry Bulk)</strong></p><p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and proactive <strong>Shipping Operations Executive</strong> to join a dynamic team managing a fleet of dry bulk vessels trading worldwide. The ideal candidate will have 2–3 years of experience in <strong>bulk shipping operations</strong>, preferably on the <strong>owners or operators desk</strong>, and a strong understanding of voyage execution, documentation, and post-fixture coordination.</p><p>This is a hands-on role that offers exposure to end-to-end vessel operations, commercial decision-making, and direct liaison with charterers, agents, and masters.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee daily voyage operations for owned and time-chartered bulk carriers.</li><li>Coordinate with ship masters, charterers, brokers, agents, and bunker suppliers to ensure smooth voyage execution.</li><li>Monitor vessel performance, port rotations, laytime, demurrage, and operational costs.</li><li>Prepare and review voyage instructions, cargo documentation, and port clearances.</li><li>Track and report vessel positions, bunker consumption, and voyage results.</li><li>Handle laytime calculations and assist with claims and post-fixture documentation.</li><li>Support the commercial team with performance analysis and voyage optimisation.</li><li>Maintain accurate operational records and ensure compliance with company and regulatory requirements.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Maritime Studies, Shipping, Logistics, or related discipline.</li><li>2–3 years of relevant experience in <strong>dry bulk operations</strong> on the <strong>owners/operators desk</strong>.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>voyage and time charter party terms</strong>, laytime and demurrage.</li><li>Familiarity with <strong>commercial shipping systems</strong> and Microsoft Office applications.</li><li>Excellent communication and coordination skills across multiple stakeholders.</li><li>Ability to multitask and work under pressure in a fast-paced environment.</li><li>Analytical mindset with attention to detail and a strong sense of accountability.</li><li>Exposure to <strong>Supramax, Panamax, or Handymax</strong> segments.</li><li>Experience with <strong>claims handling, voyage estimation tools, or bunker planning</strong>.</li><li>Proactive attitude with an interest in growing into a <strong>commercial or chartering</strong> function.</li></ul><p><strong>Location & Reporting</strong></p><ul><li>Based in Singapore.</li><li>Reports to the <strong>Operations Manager / Senior Operator</strong>.</li></ul>",
